Mashable is seeking an experienced, full-time Lifestyle Reporter to work in our New York City office. This person will write and edit informative and practical articles on a range of topics including health, fitness, style, relationships, education&mdash;and all through the prism of digital.</p>
<p>
We&rsquo;re looking for a gifted writer who can not only report on these myriad topics, but is willing to, where possible, report through first-hand experience.</p>
<p>
The ideal candidate should be a social media citizen, with active, visible accounts on Twitter, Facebook, Vine, and Instagram.</p>
<p>
We&rsquo;re looking for quality, a snappy, entertaining writing style and the ability to hit the ground running (self-starters need only apply).</p>
<p>
Curious about the kind of stories you might write as our Lifestyles Reporter. Here are some example ideas:</p>
<ul>
<li>
10 Ways Social Media is Fixing Broken Marriages</li>
<li>
Your Mind on Facebook: How It&#39;s Changing the Way We See Ourselves</li>
<li>
25 Technologies that Will Turn Your Vacation Into a Life Altering Experience</li>
<li>
This Startup&#39;s Building the Next Revolution in Fitness Technology</li>
<li>
Reinventing Your Bathroom for the 21st Century</li>
</ul>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Developing, pursuing and publishing multiple stories in a day</li>
<li>
Working&nbsp; with Lifestyle Channel Editor to identify, pursue and deliver strategic posts</li>
<li>
Editing</li>
<li>
Line edit numerous 200 to 800-word articles each day</li>
<li>
Some travel to events and conferences</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Requirements:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Bachelor&#39;s degree (BA/BS) from a four-year, accredited college or university</li>
<li>
2 or more years of experience with a daily news website, and/or lifestyle/general interest news website</li>
<li>
Comfort/familiarity with technology</li>
<li>
A year or more of experience editing writers -- line-editing as well as copy-editing</li>
<li>
Familiarity with HTML</li>
<li>
Familiarity with Photo Editing tools: Photoshop, Picasa</li>
<li>
